00:51:57,820 --> 00:51:58,539
...plus...

986
00:51:58,900 --> 00:51:59,619
...nine.

987
00:51:59,619 --> 00:52:00,119
Whoa.

988
00:52:00,119 --> 00:52:02,860
No wonder why you took him as a guide, he's very persuasive.

989
00:52:02,860 --> 00:52:04,380
Yeah, very persuasive.

990
00:52:04,380 --> 00:52:05,980
Uh, it looks to you...

991
00:52:05,980 --> 00:52:10,039
...and then it looks down at the bodies there, and starts moving...

992
00:52:10,039 --> 00:52:11,760
Yummy, yum, yum!

993
00:52:11,760 --> 00:52:16,559
...starts moving slowly towards the charred, unconscious man.

994
00:52:16,559 --> 00:52:19,340
I'm gonna move away from him, because I did just pull him out of the fire.

995
00:52:19,340 --> 00:52:20,340
Yeah, let's all move away.

996
00:52:20,340 --> 00:52:24,039
I'm just gonna back up slowly, but I'm gonna raise my arm so I look really big.

997
00:52:24,039 --> 00:52:28,760
Uh, I'm gonna Homer Simpson into the shrub, just like, just vanish slowly.

998
00:52:29,380 --> 00:52:34,079
Um, you see, as you all kind of back away and disperse from the scene,

999
00:52:34,299 --> 00:52:41,059
the bugbear, like, senses that the guy is still alive, and takes one swipe across its throat,

1000
00:52:41,059 --> 00:52:44,440
and then starts dragging the bodies back into its cave.

1001
00:52:44,440 --> 00:52:45,440
With the knife still on the body?

1002
00:52:45,440 --> 00:52:47,219
With the knife still tucked into his shirt?

1003
00:52:47,219 --> 00:52:52,099
Well, I may have forgotten to actually tuck it in the shirt, I was gonna, you know?

1004
00:52:52,099 --> 00:52:56,799
I was really meanin' to do it, but you know, there's a lot happenin' at the time!

1005
00:52:56,799 --> 00:53:01,039
It falls off, just bumps off right at the mouth of the cave.

1006
00:53:01,219 --> 00:53:02,219
Does it start singing?

1007
00:53:02,219 --> 00:53:03,219
Jump?

1008
00:53:03,219 --> 00:53:05,739
Is that pulling it out of its scabbard?

1009
00:53:05,739 --> 00:53:08,019
Did you sheath it when you put it back?

1010
00:53:08,019 --> 00:53:09,900
I never put it in a shirt.

1011
00:53:09,900 --> 00:53:10,900
Oh.

1012
00:53:10,900 --> 00:53:15,219
Don't leave me now.

1013
00:53:15,219 --> 00:53:16,579
How could I?

1014
00:53:16,579 --> 00:53:22,179
Gru come back, don't leave me now.

1015
00:53:22,179 --> 00:53:25,219
I'm here for you, darlin', I got you, I got you!

1016
00:53:25,219 --> 00:53:28,500
Gru, you run over, make a dexterity saving throw.

1017
00:53:28,500 --> 00:53:34,280
Uh, fourteen plus six, twenty.

1018
00:53:34,280 --> 00:53:41,119
You run to the dagger as it's singing towards you, and you pick it up, and narrowly miss

1019
00:53:41,119 --> 00:53:46,559
a giant claw that comes out and tries to pull you into the cave as you back up.

1020
00:53:46,559 --> 00:53:49,280
Well, I'm big!

1021
00:53:49,280 --> 00:53:50,760
Talk about disrespect!

1022
00:53:50,760 --> 00:53:55,159
Gave you two bodies!

1023
00:53:55,159 --> 00:53:58,839
Not one, but two bodies.

1024
00:53:58,839 --> 00:53:59,839
Two bodies.

1025
00:53:59,839 --> 00:54:00,839
Two bodies.

1026
00:54:00,839 --> 00:54:01,839
Two bodies.

1027
00:54:01,839 --> 00:54:09,519
Anybody got a sheath for this thing, cause it won't stop singing?

1028
00:54:09,519 --> 00:54:10,920
What happened to the one you had?

1029
00:54:10,920 --> 00:54:12,559
Is it the one still on your body?

1030
00:54:12,559 --> 00:54:13,559
Did you like?

1031
00:54:13,559 --> 00:54:14,559
Oh, yeah.

1032
00:54:14,559 --> 00:54:15,559
Yeah, that's a good idea.

1033
00:54:15,559 --> 00:54:17,199
Alright, I'll sheath it.

1034
00:54:17,199 --> 00:54:24,719
Okay, well maybe we go back to the river, and we all just kinda go our separate ways,

1035
00:54:24,960 --> 00:54:27,160
and never talk about the situation again.

1036
00:54:27,160 --> 00:54:30,440
Yeah, no, it makes sense, yeah.

1037
00:54:30,440 --> 00:54:33,360
The four of you walk back to the river where the ship was.

1038
00:54:33,360 --> 00:54:34,360
Was?

1039
00:54:34,360 --> 00:54:35,360
Hmm, was.

1040
00:54:35,360 --> 00:54:36,360
And see-

1041
00:54:36,360 --> 00:54:41,800
I may have tethered the lines and put a hole in it so it would sink so no one

1042
00:54:41,800 --> 00:54:45,920
could use it, cause I was afraid I was gonna be followed, you see.

1043
00:54:45,920 --> 00:54:49,480
The ship now sits at the bottom of the river with a flag sticking up out of it

1044
00:54:49,480 --> 00:54:53,920
that is singed and on fire.

1045
00:54:53,920 --> 00:54:56,159
But I didn't light it on fire, that wasn't me.

